I don't think it about the relationship part. I think it's more of the "being loner" part that the hentai missed the mark. Being alone isn't about "everyones dumb but me", it's more that we can't go about life like drunkards. For us, life is a greater danger: we are made of glass -woe unto us if we bump against something! And all is lost if we fall! Therefore we reflect more and do less. Combined with the fact that we are constantly pushed away by peoples, or rather, we push people away from us, to protect ourselves we build an unbreachable castle around us. That fact that the guy lowerd his defense so easily is yet but another betrayal.

Also I've been in a situation like this albeit in college where I helped this girl in C language programming and ever since we've became interested to each other. But it did come to nowhere though as both of us we're afraid to make the first move and because of that, we became distant to each other as time goes by.
